<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<Data CreatedBy="admin" CreatedOn="634301774490686186" UpdatedBy="admin" UpdatedOn="634305160265322330">
  <Properties />
  <Nodes>
    <Header Code="HeaderElement1" Type="Title" ShowInTOC="1"><![CDATA[The object model]]></Header>
    <Paragraph Code="ParagraphElement1"><![CDATA[<p>The RibbonBar control is a complex control visually similar to&nbsp;a ToolBar. The difference is additional separation of tool items to <em>Pages. </em>The Page is top level container object&nbsp;with special visual appearance. The additional separation of tool items inside a Page is available with Groups. Group of items is shown on the Page&nbsp;as a frame with caption (text).<br /><br />The hierarchy of objects&nbsp;is:</p><p><strong>RibbonBar </strong>control<strong><br /></strong>&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>Page</strong> - top level&nbsp;object&nbsp;of&nbsp;<em>RibbonBarPage&nbsp;</em>type, a container of Groups<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>Group</strong> - second level&nbsp;object of&nbsp;<em>RibbonBarGroup&nbsp;</em>type, a container of Items<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>Item</strong> - a tool item shown inside of&nbsp;Group boundaries, is a single Item or a container of SubItems<br />&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong>SubItem</strong><strong> - </strong>a tool item shown inside of Item boundaries with a predefined layout</p><p>The Item could be a one of four different types:</p><ul><li>RibbonBarButtonItem</li><li>RibbonBarDropDownButtonItem</li><li>RibbonBarStackItem</li><li>RibbonBarFlowItem</li></ul>]]></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Code="ParagraphElement2"><![CDATA[<p>Item types inherit from <em>RibbonBarItem </em>abstract<em> </em>base type. <br />The base type defines common properties:</p><ul><li><em>Text - </em>a text shown under the item as a caption (System.String)</li><li><em>Tag - </em>an&nbsp;object associated with item to implement application logic (System.Object)</li><li><em>ToolTip - </em>a text shown when mouse goes over the item (System.String)&nbsp;</li><li><em>Visible - </em>a boolean to determine whether to show or hide the item (System.Boolean)</li><li><em>Enabled - </em>a boolean to determine whether the item is responsive&nbsp;to click events  (System.Boolean)</li></ul>]]></Paragraph>
    <Header Code="HeaderElement2" Type="Title" ShowInTOC="1"><![CDATA[RibbonBarButtonItem]]></Header>
    <Paragraph Code="ParagraphElement3"><![CDATA[<p>This type of tool item represents a button. The click on the button could be handled to implement application logic.<br />The RibbonBarButtonItem type is a single item, defines:</p><ul><li>Click&nbsp;event - happens when the item is mouse clicked, use designer to provide code for event handler</li><li>Image property - a resource handle to display an image on the button</li></ul>]]></Paragraph>
    <Header Code="HeaderElement3" Type="Title" ShowInTOC="1"><![CDATA[RibbonBarDropDownButtonItem]]></Header>
    <Paragraph Code="ParagraphElement4"><![CDATA[<p>This type of tool item represents a button with a dropdown menu of items.<br />In addition to common properties of base class described above, it defines:</p><ul><li>DropDownMenu&nbsp;property&nbsp;- a ContextMenu to display on button click&nbsp;</li><li>Image property&nbsp;<strong>- </strong>a resource handle to display image on the button</li></ul>]]></Paragraph>
    <Header Code="HeaderElement4" Type="Title" ShowInTOC="1"><![CDATA[RibbonBarStackItem]]></Header>
    <Paragraph Code="ParagraphElement5"><![CDATA[<p>This type of tool item represents a Panel based container of vertically stacked SubItems.<br />The SubItems could be one of following types:</p><ul><li>RibbonBarButtonItem</li><li>RibbonBarDropDownButtonItem</li><li>RibbonBarCheckBoxItem</li><li>RibbonBarTextBoxItem</li><li>RibbonBarComboBoxItem</li><li>RibbonBarToolbarItem</li></ul>]]></Paragraph>
    <Header Code="HeaderElement5" Type="Title" ShowInTOC="1"><![CDATA[RibbonBarFlowItem]]></Header>
    <Paragraph Code="ParagraphElement6"><![CDATA[<p>This type of tool item represents a container based on FlowLayoutPanel. The default flow direction is Left to Right.<br />The SubItems are shown with flow layout from left to right taking the available width of&nbsp;RibbonBarFlowItem. You can set the <em>Width </em>property<em>&nbsp;</em>of&nbsp;RibbonBarFlowItem in the designer. To add SubItems to RibbonBarFlowItem&nbsp;open&nbsp;<em>Items </em>collection in the designer.<br />The SubItems could be one of following types:</p><ul><li>RibbonBarButtonItem</li><li>RibbonBarDropDownButtonItem</li><li>RibbonBarCheckBoxItem</li><li>RibbonBarTextBoxItem</li><li>RibbonBarComboBoxItem</li><li>RibbonBarToolbarItem</li></ul>]]></Paragraph>
    <Header Code="HeaderElement6" Type="Title" ShowInTOC="1"><![CDATA[SubItem Types]]></Header>
    <Paragraph Code="ParagraphElement7"><![CDATA[<p>There are 6 SubItems types available out of the box:</p><ul><li>RibbonBarButtonItem - a button with Click event and Image property</li><li>RibbonBarDropDownButtonItem - a button with drop down menu, MenuClick event and Image properties</li><li>RibbonBarCheckBoxItem - a checkbox item</li><li>RibbonBarTextBoxItem - a textbox item</li><li>RibbonBarComboBoxItem - a combobox item</li><li>RibbonBarToolbarItem - a container of SubItems</li></ul><p>Full set of events and properties of underlying controls is available programmatically.<br />The base class of all item and SubItem types is <em>RibbonBarItem</em>&nbsp;that defines <em>Control</em> property. Cast this property to a specific class like Button, CheckBox, TextBox, ComboBox, Panel or FlowLayoutPanel to access properties and to provide event handlers.&nbsp;<br />RibbonBarToolbarItem is Panel based container type of&nbsp;<em>RibbonBarToolBarButtonItem</em>'s. This type is an additional way to aggregate tool items.</p>]]></Paragraph>
    <Header Code="HeaderElement7" Type="Title" ShowInTOC="1"><![CDATA[Partial Class diagram]]></Header>
    <Image Code="ImageElement1" Resource="ClassDiagram.png" Type="Resource" />
    <Paragraph Code="ParagraphElement8"><![CDATA[<p>The class diagram available for download in <a target="_blank" href="http://argouml.tigris.org/">ArgoUML</a> model.</p>]]></Paragraph>
